  "text": "## SpiderMonkey JIT Compilation Pipeline - Key Files\n\nThe Firefox SpiderMonkey JavaScript engine's JIT compilation pipeline is orchestrated through several key files in `js/src/jit/`:\n\n### 1. Top-Level Ion Compiler Orchestration\n**File:** `js/src/jit/Ion.cpp` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Key Symbol:** `IonCompile()` (static function at line 1765)\n\nThe `IonCompile` function is the main entry point for the Ion optimizing compiler. It:\n- Allocates and initializes compilation state (TempAllocator, MIRGraph, CompileInfo, MIRGenerator)\n- Creates a WarpSnapshot for the compilation\n- Either schedules off-thread compilation via `IonCompileTask` or performs synchronous back-end compilation\n- Manages linking of compiled code\n\n### 2. Off-Thread Compilation Task\n**Header:** `js/src/jit/IonCompileTask.h` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Source:** `js/src/jit/IonCompileTask.cpp` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Key Class:** `IonCompileTask` (line 27 in header)\n\nThe `IonCompileTask` class represents a single off-thread Ion compilation task. It:\n- Inherits from `HelperThreadTask` and `mozilla::LinkedListElement<IonCompileTask>`\n- Holds the MIRGenerator and optional CodeGenerator (backgroundCodegen_)\n- Implements `runTask()` to compile the backend on helper threads\n- Implements `runHelperThreadTask()` to integrate results back on the main thread\n\n### 3. First-Tier JIT Compiler (Baseline)\n**Header:** `js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.h` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Source:** `js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.cpp` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Key Class:** `BaselineScript` (line 189 in header)\n\nThe `BaselineScript` class represents the compiled output of the Baseline JIT compiler (first-tier, faster to compile). It:\n- Uses trailing array layout for memory efficiency (resumeEntryList, retAddrEntries, osrEntries, debugTrapEntries)\n- Stores the compiled JitCode method pointer and pending Ion compilation tasks\n- Provides OSR (On-Stack Replacement) entries for transitioning to Ion code\n- Manages debug instrumentation and profiler toggles\n\n### 4. Per-Runtime JIT State\n**Header:** `js/src/jit/JitRuntime.h` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Key Class:** `JitRuntime` (defined in header)\n\nThe `JitRuntime` class manages per-runtime JIT compilation state:\n- Maintains BaselineICFallbackCode for IC stubs\n- Tracks IonCompileTask lists (ionLazyLinkList_)\n- Manages off-thread compilation task batches\n- Stores pre-generated trampoline code for VM functions\n- Integrates Ion compilation tasks for lazy linking on the main thread\n\n### 5. JIT Configuration Options\n**Header:** `js/src/jit/JitOptions.h` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Source:** `js/src/jit/JitOptions.cpp` (repo: github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8)\n**Key Class/Struct:** `DefaultJitOptions` (line 46 in header)\n\nThe `DefaultJitOptions` struct (exposed as global `JitOptions`) controls JIT configuration:\n- Baseline interpreter and JIT thresholds (baselineInterpreterWarmUpThreshold, baselineJitWarmUpThreshold)\n- Ion compilation thresholds (normalIonWarmUpThreshold)\n- Optimization passes (inlining, GVN, range analysis, scalar replacement, etc.)\n- Register allocator selection\n- Spectre mitigation flags\n- Debug and profiling options\n\n### Compilation Pipeline Flow\n\n1. **Entry:** Script execution triggers `IonCompile()` in Ion.cpp when warm-up thresholds are met\n2. **Preparation:** MIRGenerator and graph are created with optimization info from JitOptions\n3. **Off-Thread Decision:** If `options.offThreadCompilationAvailable()`, create IonCompileTask and schedule on helper thread\n4. **Back-End Compilation:** Call `CompileBackEnd()` which generates machine code from MIR\n5. **Linking:** Call `LinkCodeGen()` to finalize the IonScript and integrate with JitRuntime\n6. **Fallback:** BaselineScript serves as first-tier JIT for faster initial compilation, with OSR capability to reach Ion code\n\nThis architecture enables SpiderMonkey to rapidly compile code with Baseline JIT while continuing to optimize hot code paths with the Ion compiler on background threads."
}

